11/04/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government has endorsed an action plan for the transfer of responsibilities and financial resources under the decentralisation process, according to a press release Friday (8 April). 
The plan includes a detailed schedule of all activities related to local government reform to be implemented in the next six months. 
It is focused on certain sectors such as healthcare, education, social protections, utility services, culture and finance. 
The document is part of the 2004-2007 Decentralisation Programme adopted by the government in accordance with the Ohrid Peace Agreement. 
The government also decided that the relevant ministries should prepare public information campaigns aimed at introducing the process of local government reform to residents. 
(Macedonian Government Web site, A1 TV - 08/04/05)
